column4: Principal\rdebra.mclaren@cvesd.org\rwww.camarenaelementary.com\r\r2018-19 School Accountability Report Card\r-\r---Published During the 2019-20 School Year\r\rSchool Description\rCamarena Elementary School is the second newest of 49 schools
column6: in the Chula\rVista Elementary School District. Camarena School opened in July
column7: 2013 and is located in the\rWinding Walk community of Eastlake.  The school facility consists of two 2-story buildings that\rcontain 32 classrooms and three one-story buildings that contain 12 additional classrooms for a\rtotal of 44 classrooms. Every classroom contains a flat screen TV and Apple TV for projection from\rteacher and student digital devices.  Classrooms have white board paint across one wall from floor\r--------\rto 8 feet to allow for student brainstorming and exploration of ideas. The Library Media Center is\rChula Vista Elementary School\ran open space with two flat screen TVs on either side of the space. There is a Green Screen Video\rDistrict\rRoom within the Library Media Center to provide opportunities for broadcast and video production.\r84 East J Street\rChula Vista
